line_1: To keep the days on Zion's mount,
line_2: And send the year to his account,

line_1: To clear Euphrates, and the secret mount,
line_2: All which the sacred bard would oft recount:

line_1: Doubts not hereafter with the saints to mount,
line_2: She, half an angel in her own account,

line_1: So to the dark-brow'd wood, or sacred mount,
line_2: And, led in vision, drank at Siloe's fount,
There would I thy power recount,

line_1: In visiting Airy, and seeing his Mount:
line_2: I hope, Sir, by this you have found your Account,

line_1: Make fair deductions, see to what they mount?
line_2: Bring then these Blessings to a strict account,

line_1: Deard's bill for baubles shall to thousands mount,
line_2: And I'd out-di'mond even the di'mond count.

line_1: Him mourn'd all the Dryads on CLAVERTON's Mount;
line_2: Him AVON deplor'd, Him the Nymph of the Fount,
And cities, seas, and kingdoms count:
